    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-11-19T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-11-19T13:00:00-05:00" n="1030"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1030">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">745W.00/11–1952: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1030<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom (<persName
                            corresp="#p_GWS1" type="from">Gifford</persName>) to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1030fn1">Repeated to Cairo as telegram 154, to Khartoum as
                        telegram 5, and unnumbered to Paris for Reinhardt and to Rome for <persName
                            corresp="#p_UL1">Unger</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-11-19T18:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 19, 1952—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2861. Fol is abbreviated text statement on Sudan (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                        >Embtel</gloss> 2798 Nov 15) which Stevenson has now been instructed discuss
                    with <persName corresp="#p_NGM1">Naguib</persName>, probably tomorrow:</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="italic">Begin Text</hi>.</p>
                    <p>
                        <gloss target="#t_HMG1">HMG</gloss> and Egypt Govt firmly believe in right
                        of Sudanese to self-determination and effective exercise thereof at proper
                        time and with necessary safeguards.</p>
                    <list>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Two govts agree that in order enable Sudanese to exercise
                            self-determination in free and neutral atmosphere, transitional period
                            proved in full self-govt for Sudanese shall begin forthwith.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Two govts further agree this transitional period shall be considered
                            as period of preparation for effective termination dual administration
                            and that during transitional period sovereignty of Sudan shall be kept
                            in reserve for Sudanese until self-determination achieved.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Further agreed between two govts that in order give effect soon as
                            possible to principle enunciated above, a mixed comm shall be appointed
                            forthwith in connection with elections to be held in Sudan in accordance
                            self-govt statute which will shortly be promulgated. Function this comm
                            will be to observe and supervise preparations for and conduct of free
                            and impartial elections. Comm shall consist three Sudanese appointed by
                            Governor General, one Egypt, one Brit, one <persName corresp="#p_ALG1"
                                >Amer</persName> and one Indian or Pakistani, nominated by
                            respective govts, and Indian or Pakistani member shall be
                            chairman.</item>
                        <label>5.</label>
                        <item>Two govts also agree establish advisory comm of five members to advise
                            Gov-Gen in exercise certain his powers under new interim constitution.
                            Members commission shall be two Sudanese, one Egyptian, one British and
                            one Indian or Pakistani. Egyptian and British Goverments now urgently
                            considering how this comm shld be constituted, its functions and its
                            terms of ref.</item>
                        <label>6.</label>
                        <item>Two govts agree preparations for elections in Sudan shall go forward
                            notwithstanding these discussions and that newly elected Sudan
                            Parliament shall be consulted re functions of advisory comm.</item>
                    </list>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="italic">End Text</hi>.</p>
                </quote>
                <pb facs="0187" n="1889" xml:id="pg_1889"/>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> considering instructing Stevenson
                    alter foregoing before discussion with <persName corresp="#p_NGM1"
                        >Naguib</persName> by specifying Indian member for election comm in para 4
                    and Pakistani on advisory comm in para 5.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GWS1">
                            <hi rend="strong">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gifford</hi>
                            </hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
